https://orcaforum.kofo.mpg.de/app.php/portal  for downloading the last version of ORCA, manuals, and participate in forums. (Avogadro can also be found here)
 
https://www.orcasoftware.de/tutorials_orca/ for ORCA tutorials

https://www.ccdc.cam.ac.uk/ for the Cambridge Crystallographic Data Centre

https://www.ccdc.cam.ac.uk/solutions/csd-core/components/mercury/ for downloading Mercury (it would be needed to handle the files from the CCDC)

https://slurm.schedmd.com/overview.html    information about SLURM

https://sites.google.com/site/orcainputlibrary/home?authuser=0  more ORCA tutorials

https://www.easyspin.org/   for easyspin download ( Matlab is needed to run it)

https://pubs.acs.org/doi/10.1021/acs.jchemed.0c00959 Educational paper on ORCA
